mitre_attack_techniques.signature_description: hide graphical window
link many functions at runtime
Adversaries may configure system settings to automatically execute a program during system boot or logon to maintain persistence or gain higher-level privileges on compromised systems.
Adversaries may achieve persistence by adding a program to a startup folder or referencing it with a Registry run key.
Adversaries may communicate using application layer protocols to avoid detection/network filtering by blending in with existing traffic.

Adversaries may interact with the Windows Registry to hide configuration information within Registry keys, remove information as part of cleaning up, or as part of other techniques to aid in persistence and execution.
Adversaries may attempt to get information about running processes on a system.
Creates an autostart registry key
Spawns processes
Drops PE files to the user root directory (C:\\Documents and Settings\\User or C:\\Users\\User)
Creates files inside the user directory
Drops PE files to the user directory
May sleep (evasive loops) to hinder dynamic analysis
Queries a list of all running processes
Reads ini files
Queries the cryptographic machine GUID
Reads software policies
Queries the volume information (name, serial number etc) of a device
Reads the hosts file
Tries to download or post to a non-existing http route (HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found / 503 Service Unavailable)
Posts data to webserver
Performs DNS lookups

Posts data to webserver
Performs DNS lookups
Passes username and password via HTTP get
Found C&C like URL pattern
Uses a known web browser user agent for HTTP communication

signature_matches.name: link function at runtime on Windows
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: link function at runtime on Windows
    namespace: linking/runtime-linking
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: instruction
      dynamic: call
    att&ck:
      - Execution::Shared Modules [T1129]
    examples:
      - 9324D1A8AE37A36AE560C37448C9705A:0x404130
      - Practical Malware Analysis Lab 01-04.exe_:0x401350
  features:
    - and:
      - os: windows
      - or:
        - api: kernel32.GetProcAddress
        - api: ntdll.LdrGetProcedureAddress

signature_matches.name: hide graphical window
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: hide graphical window
    namespace: host-interaction/gui/window/hide
    authors:
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: basic block
      dynamic: call
    att&ck:
      - Defense Evasion::Hide Artifacts::Hidden Window [T1564.003]
    examples:
      - 39C05B15E9834AC93F206BC114D0A00C357C888DB567BA8F5345DA0529CBED41:0x10007250
  features:
    - and:
      - number: 0x0 = SW_HIDE
      - api: user32.ShowWindow

signature_matches.name: link many functions at runtime
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: link many functions at runtime
    namespace: linking/runtime-linking
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
      - joakim@intezer.com
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: thread
    att&ck:
      - Execution::Shared Modules [T1129]
    examples:
      - b7b5e1253710d8927cbe07d52d2d2e10:0x401000
  features:
    - or:
      - and:
        - os: windows
        - match: link function at runtime on Windows
        - or:
          - count(api(kernel32.GetProcAddress)): 5 or more
          - count(api(ntdll.LdrGetProcedureAddress)): 5 or more
      - and:
        - or:
          - os: linux
          - os: android
        - match: link function at runtime on Linux
        - or:
          - count(api(dlsym)): 5 or more
          - count(api(dlvsym)): 5 or more

signature_matches.name: terminate process
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: terminate process
    namespace: host-interaction/process/terminate
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
      - anushka.virgaonkar@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: thread
    mbc:
      - Process::Terminate Process [C0018]
    examples:
      - C91887D861D9BD4A5872249B641BC9F9:0x401A77
      - 9B7CCAA2AE6A5B96E3110EBCBC4311F6:0x10010307
  features:
    - or:
      - api: System.Diagnostics.Process::Kill
      - api: System.Diagnostics.Process::WaitForExit
      - api: System.Diagnostics.Process::WaitForExitAsync
      - api: System.Environment::Exit
      - api: System.Windows.Forms.Application::Exit
      - api: exit
      - api: Exit
      - and:
        - optional:
          - match: open process
        - or:
          - api: kernel32.TerminateProcess
          - api: ntdll.NtTerminateProcess
          - api: kernel32.ExitProcess
